$interpreted: Chiyuki: The Last Orchid? So you're... the Master devoted to the pursuit of flawless beauty?
Master Orchid: Flawless... There is no such perfection in this world. What I search for is—
Master Orchid: The limit of beauty.
Chiyuki: The limit of beauty...?
Master Orchid: The truest and most germinal boundary, a split-second of eternity.
Chiyuki: (Is this idiot really the one they all call the Master?)
Master Orchid: Hehehehe. You must have been expecting someone different, to judge by the confused look on your face.
Chiyuki: I'm sorry...
Master Orchid: Don't worry about it, I'm never as people imagine me to be. The mountain pass is steep—why have you come here alone?
Chiyuki: Because...
Chiyuki: (...I'm here now. I might as well give this a try.)
Chiyuki: To be honest, I'd heard of your great accomplishments, and wanted to study under you.
Master Orchid: Is that so. Hmm~
Master Orchid: Hmm~ Snow-white cheeks, tender skin...
Chiyuki: (How long will this go on for... I'm totally unprepared...)
Master Orchid: Your appearance looks quite outstanding to me. You've nurtured your beauty well, too.
Chiyuki: You can tell, Master?
Master Orchid: In the pursuit of beauty, each and every effort will leave its trace. That said, with you looking this gorgeous, what more could I offer you?
Chiyuki: I... I don't think it's enough.
Chiyuki: I don't know how to explain it. No matter how much I try, it never feels like enough.
Master Orchid: Then allow me to ask you, what exactly are you searching for?
Chiyuki: I'm searching for...
Chiyuki: I want to be crowned Alliance Beauty in the upcoming Martial Arts Tourney.
Master Orchid: Oh, Alliance Beauty...
Chiyuki: (Is that all he can say? Perhaps he thinks that's too tacky...)
Master Orchid: What do you think beauty is?
Chiyuki: Beauty? Isn't beauty... just beauty?
Master Orchid: ......
Chiyuki: (Oh no, I'm jibbering again. There must be some hidden meaning in the Master's question.)
Chiyuki: (Beauty is what's pleasing to an audience... No, that's too simple. Beauty makes people happy... no, that doesn't sound right either.)
Chiyuki: (Beauty brings people joy... What on earth am I saying...)
Chiyuki: (Beauty, beauty, beauty... What in the world is it...)
Master Orchid: Enough.
Master Orchid: Since you can't put it into words, try expressing it with movement.
Chiyuki: Where did all these people come from...
Master Orchid: They've all come here on their spiritual quests, searching for the limit of beauty.
Master Orchid: Here, let your beauty shine through for everybody to see.
Chiyuki: What?
Master Orchid: In any form you like. Just let it all out.
Chiyuki: (Let my beauty shine... It's too simple. I'm Hanazono Chiyuki, I must have done that thousands of times already.)
Chiyuki: (This is so strange, why's everybody so quiet?)
Chiyuki: (Why don't they have any reaction? Normally everybody'd be applauding by now.)
Dozing Disciple: So, what d'you think?
Yawning Disciple: Hoooahh~~~ Boring.
Chiyuki: (Boring!?)
Irritated Disciple: Vulgar, simply vulgar.
Chiyuki: (V-vulgar!? What do they mean!)
Chiyuki: (Maybe I'm not perfect, but am I really such a catastrophe?)
Chiyuki: Master...
Master Orchid: Just watch.
Chiyuki: (What's he going to do?)
Master Orchid: The beauty of a flower awash in spring's breezes—
Chiyuki: (Where's that wind coming from all of a sudden? And so fresh and clean...)
Master Orchid: Drive out your worries, your melancholy, and bathe yourself in the moment—
Chiyuki: (Huh!? He's glowing!)
Chiyuki: (It's so bright! This light, it's...)
Master Orchid: [Springtime Bloom]!
Chiyuki: It's so... so pretty...
Chiyuki: What's happening? There's a field of flowers blossoming in my mind...
Chiyuki: No! It's not in my mind, it's right where I'm standing!
Chiyuki: It's as if my soul is being cleansed in their gentle, peaceful aroma. I feel like I'm in some kind of... flower fairyland.
Chiyuki: And now they've vanished.
Master Orchid: Did you see?
Chiyuki: Eh!?
Chiyuki: It was all an illusion...?
Chiyuki: No, I definitely felt it. I felt them brushing past my skin, and I smelt their sweet fragrance...
Delighted Disciple: Ahh~! He truly is the Last Orchid. He transports us to ecstasy with his beauty.
Rapturous Disciple: That was just fabulous~ The flowers blooming all over, their scents lingering in the air~
Chiyuki: (They all saw it too, I wasn't dreaming!)
Chiyuki: Master, how did you do that?
Master Orchid: I didn't do anything. I was just being myself, same as you.
Chiyuki: But how? I felt what just happened with every inch of my body...
Master Orchid: Heheh, looks like you're a sensitive one, too.
Master Orchid: It isn't easy to explain with words, but if you insist... Have you ever heard of something called star power?
Chiyuki: Hmm, I think so.
Master Orchid: All I did was let my star power shine. It stimulated your senses and that in turn produced your visions.
Master Orchid: What you witnessed could only have been seen by the most sensitive of people.
Chiyuki: But... but isn't that just how people are born?
Master Orchid: You think I was born with sensitivity? That all these people didn't work hard to get to where they are now?
Chiyuki: Sorry, that's not what I meant...
Master Orchid: We're born with our appearances, but our characters come from within us. We develop them ourselves.
Chiyuki: From within... So that's the meaning of true beauty...
Chiyuki: Attractiveness, allure, glamor... I was so wide of the mark. I've been so shallow all this time.
Master Orchid: Chiyuki, my girl.
Chiyuki: Master...
Master Orchid: What a foolish life you've been living! Beauty could never be so simple as that!
Master Orchid: The people here would happily give their entire lives over to their quest for beauty. If you let your confidence be rocked at the slightest push,
Master Orchid: you'll never understand the true meaning of beauty!
Chiyuki: ......
Chiyuki: Master Orchid, you're right! Please, allow me to study under you here!
Master Orchid: Beauty refuses no one. Your studies begin tomorrow at dawn.
Chiyuki: Yes, Master!
